  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2004",
  "title": "Cannot addDisjunctiveFacet from widget init method",
  "body": "I'm trying to add a `disjunctiveFacetRefinement` in my `init` method of a widget.\r\n\r\nI initially got an error stating > productType.name is not defined in the disjunctiveFacets attribute of the helper configuration.\r\n\r\nSo, I tried to add it with `state.addDisjunctiveFacet('productType.name');`. No luck, same error.\r\nHowever, if I manually `.push` that on to the array, it works. \r\n\r\nWhy is that? Bug, or am I doing something wrong?\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport let widget = function widget(options) {\r\n  return {\r\n    init: function({helper, state}) {\r\n\r\n      // This doesn't work\r\n      state.addDisjunctiveFacet('productType.name');\r\n\r\n      // This works\r\n      state.disjunctiveFacets.push('productType.name');\r\n      \r\n      helper.addDisjunctiveFacetRefinement('productType.name', 'Kayak');\r\n    },\r\n  };\r\n};\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n>>>\r\n\"instantsearch.js\": \"^1.10.3\",\r\n\"algoliasearch-helper\": \"^2.18.1\",\r\n",
